Android Transfer


 


Android Transfer

Version - 1.2


Description


Android Transfer shares the device's internal storage over Wi-Fi or Hotspot for easy transfer and access of files to/from the device.

Features

- Shares internal storage over wifi and hotspot
- QR code for quick access
- Can use the device while transferring files to/from device
- Supports all android versions through Android 4.4 (Kitkat)


Instructions

Creating and connecting to the server

1. Make sure that the device has successfully been connected to a wifi or hotspot network before launching Android Transfer app.
2. Open the app only after successful connection of wifi or hotspot network.
3. Android Transfer won't launch without wifi or hotspot network connection.
4. Devices should be connected to the same wifi network.

Disconnecting the server

Default method
1. While using the device during file transfer or after finishing all the file transfers, make sure to disconnect the server by long pressing the QR code.

Other alternative methods
2. Clear the recent apps.
3. Restart the device.


Note

1. Internal Storage should be in '/storage/emulated/0' format.
2. The browser should not be too old as also Internet Explorer has been replaced by Microsoft Edge.
3. Do not uninstall the installer as if done so, then Android Transfer won't be receiving future updates.
4. After transferring of files is done, disconnect the server by long pressing the QR code.
